{"entity":{"id":"recC8rTUHyDLgnCoU","type":"chapter","slug":"recC8rTUHyDLgnCoU","label":"Job.4","rawId":"recC8rTUHyDLgnCoU","book":{"id":"recOA8nVVhKs30PSI","type":"book","slug":"job","label":"Job","subtitle":"Poetry-Wisdom","count":1070,"description":"42 chapters, 190 people, 6 places"}},"stats":{"verses":21,"people":2,"places":0,"events":1},"nodes":[{"id":"recC8rTUHyDLgnCoU","type":"chapter","group":"focus","label":"Job.4","slug":"job_4","score":21},{"id":"recOA8nVVhKs30PSI","type":"book","group":"book","label":"Job","slug":"job","score":1070},{"id":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"God","slug":"god_1324","score":2},{"id":"recE1c6dLNGYPFRiW","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"Eliphaz","slug":"eliphaz_1145","score":1},{"id":"recMNT9RB1RJiLlYW","type":"event","group":"event","label":"Job's Trial","slug":"event-117","score":21}],"links":[{"source":"recC8rTUHyDLgnCoU","target":"recOA8nVVhKs30PSI","label":"part of"},{"source":"recC8rTUHyDLgnCoU","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recC8rTUHyDLgnCoU","target":"recE1c6dLNGYPFRiW","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recC8rTUHyDLgnCoU","target":"recMNT9RB1RJiLlYW","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recL6WZXsbaMTZk1c","ref":"Job.4.1","text":"Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said,","year":-1520},{"id":"rec4MdTSrZPmtpd9G","ref":"Job.4.2","text":"If we assay to commune with thee, wilt thou be grieved? but who can withhold himself from speaking?","year":-1520},{"id":"rec8PJMveQxnVRVwn","ref":"Job.4.3","text":"Behold, thou hast instructed many, and thou hast strengthened the weak hands.","year":-1520},{"id":"reccAXgX1kDAcedXA","ref":"Job.4.4","text":"Thy words have upholden him that was falling, and thou hast strengthened the feeble knees.","year":-1520},{"id":"recWEqfJXCNKO084i","ref":"Job.4.5","text":"But now it is come upon thee, and thou faintest; it toucheth thee, and thou art troubled.","year":-1520},{"id":"recUSBzW2nPc95Z8q","ref":"Job.4.6","text":"Is not this thy fear, thy confidence, thy hope, and the uprightness of thy ways?","year":-1520},{"id":"recMFXsDV16geYpZp","ref":"Job.4.7","text":"Remember, I pray thee, who ever perished, being innocent? or where were the righteous cut off?","year":-1520},{"id":"recpcrYMr4MxK0Bi6","ref":"Job.4.8","text":"Even as I have seen, they that plow iniquity, and sow wickedness, reap the same.","year":-1520}]}
